# Local URLs never resolve in CI.
^https?://localhost
^https?://127\.0\.0\.1

# Disqus / Giscus / social share targets require an active account/thread; skip.
^https?://disqus\.com
^https?://giscus\.app

# PaperMod share buttons — Reddit rejects unauthenticated GETs (403/503) on
# its submission endpoint. The link only resolves when a real user clicks
# and goes through the submission UI. (HN submitlink was previously here
# too; removed after the ShareButtons allowlist stopped rendering it.)
^https?://(www\.)?reddit\.com/submit

# Instagram, Facebook profile pages — 429 Too Many Requests / login-wall
# redirects from GitHub runner IPs. Local lychee from a personal IP passes;
# CI does not. Same failure class as LinkedIn's 999, but neither status can
# be added to --accept without masking real errors elsewhere. See
# .claude/rules/external-link-hygiene.md.
^https?://(www\.)?instagram\.com
^https?://(www\.)?facebook\.com

# Unsplash — the marketing landing page returns 401 Unauthorized to
# non-browser user agents (including lychee's default UA). Adding 401 to
# --accept would mask real auth failures elsewhere. The photo pages and
# images.unsplash.com CDN are not affected, but we don't link those from
# the site, so a host-level ignore is the right hammer here.
^https?://(www\.)?unsplash\.com

# Site's own baseURL — DNS points nowhere until the first Fly deploy.
# Remove once the site is live.
^https?://omarcrosby\.com

# Fragile academic-reference hosts (backstops; see
# .claude/rules/external-link-hygiene.md for the full pattern list).
#
# dl.acm.org — ACM rejects non-browser user agents with 403.
^https?://dl\.acm\.org
# web.eecs.umich.edu — UMich CS preprint host has intermittent TLS chain
# issues on GitHub runners (UnknownIssuer). Applies broadly to university
# preprint hosts; add specific hosts here only after observing a failure.
^https?://web\.eecs\.umich\.edu
# ieeexplore.ieee.org — IEEE Xplore requires authentication for article links,
# returns 202/403 to unauthenticated bots.
^https?://ieeexplore\.ieee\.org
# www.gnu.org — the GNU project's servers rate-limit requests from GitHub
# runner IP ranges (shared address pool). Local lychee from a personal IP
# passes; CI reliably times out. Same failure class as Instagram/Facebook
# runner-IP rate limits — the fix is host-level ignore, not --accept.
^https?://(www\.)?gnu\.org

# Specific https://doi.org URLs whose redirect terminates on a fragile host.
# lychee matches ignore patterns against the *starting* URL and does not
# consult the redirect chain, so host-level ignores above don't cover
# doi.org indirections — each cited DOI needs its own entry.
#
# 10.1145/42372.42379 — Nejmeh (1988), NPATH complexity. Redirects to ACM.
^https?://doi\.org/10\.1145/42372\.42379$
# 10.1109/TSE.2009.70 — Buse & Weimer (2010), readability. Redirects to IEEE.
^https?://doi\.org/10\.1109/TSE\.2009\.70$
